HEADWORD: centavo
<hw>centavo</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a fractional monetary unit of
several countries such as El Salvador, St. Thomas and Principe, Brazil,
Argentina, Bolivia, Colombia, Cuba, the Dominican Republic, Ecuador, El
Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Mexico, Nicaragua, Peru, the Philippines,
and Portugal.</def>⟦br⟧
